timeline
    title Startup Infrastructure Journey: Hetzner → AWS EKS

    section 🚀 Stage 1: Hetzner Foundation
        Bootstrapped MVP launch : Self-managed K3s/Talos on Hetzner
        : PostgreSQL on Hetzner + Redis
        : GitHub Actions → kubectl apply
        : 2 vCPU / 4GB @ €5.99/mo
        
        Growth phase : Add monitoring (Grafana + Loki)
        : Enable Cloudflare in front
        : Scale to 3-node cluster

    section 🔄 Stage 2: Hetzner + EKS Hybrid
        First US customer : Provision EKS cluster (us-east-1)
        : Migrate US-facing APIs first
        : Keep EU workloads on Hetzner
        : Setup ArgoCD GitOps on EKS
        
        Compliance need : Configure AWS Secrets Manager + IRSA
        : Enable CloudTrail + GuardDuty
        : Sign BAA for future HIPAA workloads

    section 🏢 Stage 3: Full AWS EKS
        Enterprise scale : Migrate remaining workloads
        : Add Aurora Serverless for DB
        : Enable EKS Auto Mode / Fargate
        : Multi-AZ + Multi-Region
        : Full SOC 2 Type II attestation
